This is my first game from glutten's simulator games. I am very happy how much this game offers for the price!  I'm new to smart phones, yet it only had taken me a few minutes to get used to the controls which are smooth until you leap at the wrong moment against a fence, but nonetheless I think it's tolerable. Beautiful expansive map that are big; but this means you can get lost.  I am extremely pleased with my purchase and will happily be purchasing other simulators from this developer in the near future.  Downfalls I am confused or wish was fixed: As much as I love this game so far, it does have it's quirks.  1: The tutorial shows you how to move and attack but otherwise throws you out to learn yourself. 2: There were times I was in a position where I needed to pause but was unable to. Is there a pause button? 3: My third and most troublesome isn't much different from no.2, but it's about having no manual saving. I find myself nervous not sure when the game decided to autosave & if I'll loose any gameplay.  If there are any answers to my downfall list, I'd thank you for answers. If not, I would be pleased if this or future titles could be patched with a manual pause/save button.  Thank you to all or any willing to read this long but honest review. I DEEPLY RECOMMEND playing this game! It's definitely worth the price if you're a fan of animal simulators!

This is how you get a mate and kittens. To get a mate find a stray cat and attack it as if you was going to kill it. An option to bond will come up click on it.You can get a mate at level 5 and a kitten at level 15 and more kittens as you get to higher levels. When you do get to level 15, in the main menu there will be a blank cat pack member slot under your mate. There will be an option to breed. Click on it and a kitten of any color will appear.  Repeat as you unlock more slots with higher levels.
